inn1.comm: angled across Gayle, good carry first ball, left alone, chest high to Taibu
wider of off, Gayle shoulders arms
fuller, still stays wide of off, Gayle leaves it alone
closer to him, but Gayle leaves it alone again, no movement in towards him so far
makes him play this time, just back of a length, pitching off and moving away, and Gayle is beaten
maiden over, this time Gayle shoulders arms to one outside off
starts on target, pitches off, straightens a touch, played back to the bowler
around off again, watchfully played back
makes him play again, goes on with the arm, played back
slightly off, defended towards cover
shorter, and slight hint of turn, played to on
comes forward and defends one outside off, back-to-back maidens
Gayle beaten again, yet to get bat on ball, pitches on a length, close enough to off to make him play, slight movement away beats him
first touch and first runs for Gayle, reaches out for a length delivery and drives it uppishly through cover, gets three runs, not a perfect shot but into the gap
moves across a bit, and turns this one to square leg
gets a thick inside edge for a single, full delivery and he looked to drive it straight
almost yorks him, can;t drive this one, hence defended back to the bowler
then angle draws an edge this time, a thick one that flies past the slip and gets him a single
full ball, turning into the pads, Sibanda makes a diving save at midwicket
slog-sweep and a top edge, Gayle is lucky it lands safe behind square on the off side, Price is disgusted
flat delivery, punched back to the bowler
slight turn, Barath stays back and defends
keeps him in the crease, and doesn't give him room, and played to midwicket
slows this delivery down, Barath stays back and pushes it back to the bowler
Gayle yet to hit a shot off the sweet spot, gets a sort of leading edge that lands safe towards cover
on the pads, and gets an easy single wide of square leg
another thick edge goes through gully, Barath plays away from the body this time
Gayle mis-hits again, goes for the big booming drive, no feet, and gets the inside half of the bat on it, rolls along towards mid-on
plays a defensive shot, just outside off, and guides it towards point
nicely struck, still not the sweetest timing, short delivery, goes across and smashes it wide of mid-off, Price dives and gets a hand on it, which means the ball doesn't travel to the boundary
poor delivery and Gayle plays his first optimum shot, this is short and ge rocks back and pulls him over midwicket
the straighter delivery again, skids along and hurries Gayle into a defensive shot
thinking of a pull shot again, but this is not that short, and there is a touch of extra bounce, hence the shot is abroted
turning into the pad, flicked to square leg
slows this delivery down, lets it turn, and turns it towards short fine
sharp turn, but too short, and he helps it towards deep midwicket for a single
steered towards third for a single
wide outside off, Barath doesn't have anything to do with it
digs this one in short, Barath gets behind the line and turns it around the corner for a single
well bowled, pithing middle, angling towards off, defended by Gayle
no room for Gayle, getting pretty close to the stumps with that release, and pitches leg and ends up around off
similar delivery, same result, a pat towards the bowler
angled into the pads, looks to whip it but is late into the shot
pitched up to him and driven down to long-on for one
presses forward and defends outside off
shorter delivery, punched towards deep midwicket
nicely bowled, pitched middle and leg and straightens a touch, skids too, defended by Barath
into the pads, and he is late into the shot again, not judging the pace off the pitch well
goes for the pull shot, ends up playing over the ball, not short enough for the shot
flayed across the line, clears the front leg and swats this length delivery off the pads, in the air, over the leg-side infield
slower ball, back of a length, Gayle early into it, and takes the bottom hand off to keep it down and takes a single towards point
seam movement there, holds its line outside off and beats him
nice cover-drive, on a knee and over cover, nice high elbow for the pose
short ball, into the body, turned straight to square leg
drills a straight delivery straight to mid-off

shot! there are two deep fielders on the on side, but they matter little when Gayle steps out with a clear mind and makes clean connection. The ball lands on the roof of the stand behind deep midwicket and bounces off towards the ocean! New balls please
pitched up and drilled back to his right, gets a hand to it and deflects it to mid-off, enough time for a single
goes for the sweep, misses, the ball rolls along off the pads towards short fine
pushed through into the pads, gets a thick inside edge towards short fine
on the stumps again, no room, defended to cover
nicely flighted around off, slight break away, defended towards point
whatashot! just the second delivery from the new bowler, goes with the spin, inside-out, and over extra cover
makes room, Lamb follows him, and gets a safe inside edge from Gayle
full delivery, into the pads, misses out on the sweep shot
turn there, pitches leg, and turns towards middle and off, misses on the sweep shot again
pushed down the leg side, Gayle misses on the pull shot but gets a wide
defends one off the back foot
steps out of the crease, the ball dips on Barath, and he has to change the shot and defend
again late in looking to turn this to leg
dropped by Taylor at square leg, a dolly there, swept straight to him, but it goes straight through his hands
flicked wide of mid-on for a single
turning into his pads, played to short fine
flighted around off, turning in, and played to midwicket
full delivery, flicked to midwicket
sharp turn into the pads, helped along to short fine
skidding along, could have been a toppie, defended towards midwicket
fires this one in, defended back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, hit to mid-off for a single
flat delivery, outside off, hit back to the bowler
shimmies down the ground, drives him down to long-on
leading edge from Gayle who is looking for an easy single to the on side, soft hands mean it doesn't carry to the bowler
into the pads, helped away for a single to deep midwicket
turn there, stays back and plays defensively
this one doesn't turn, Barath stays back and defends
goes for the powerful shot, lands half-way to long-on, gets him a single
punches a short delivery down to long-on for a single
half-sweeps, in that he doesn't quite bend down, plays it straight to square leg
substantial turn there, Gayle is looking to play this behind square on the on side, but it turns away, making him forget that shot and play a defensive shot
outer half of the bat, pitching middle and turning away, Gayle is safe
into the pads, can't get it past midwicket
pitched middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
Barath steps down, gets to the pitch of it, and drives him down to long-on
makes a diving save to his right, saves a single

beautifully bowled and Taibu is quick as a flash! nicely flighted, it dips on him, drawing him out of the crease, searching for the delivery that pitches shorter than it seemed, and then breaks away and beats him and Taibu removes the bails in a jiffy. Big, big wicket
open-stanced already, moves across and flicks a full delivery towards midwicket
drift and turn, Chanders beaten big time, just outside off
tossed up again, this time he gets close to the pitch and plays it back to the bowler
whipped away from outside off, takes a single to long-on
short, turns away, gets the toe end on the cut shot
fuller this time, comes forward and defends
quicker delivery, going on with the arm, beating him
moves across, flicks towards square leg, wants a single, sent back
shortish, outside off, punched towards cover
moves across, covers the spin, and helps it into the on side for a single
nicely tossed up again, dips on him, Chanderpaul doesn't stretch forward, and defends in front of his body
shorter this time, quick to rock back, and cuts it into the gap past point
flat offbreak, pushes forwards to defend
presses forward and defends another offbreak
flatter, quicker delivery, opens the face of the bat, and comes through for a quick single
doesn't turn and hurries Chanders into the defensive shot
comes forward, covers the stumps, and opens the face late for a single
steps out of the crease and pushes this down to long-on
punched away uppishly, but down the ground and there is no mid-on
slightly short, stays back to punch this, but can't get it past point
extra bounce on a similar delivery, punches it to point again
pitches on a length, around middle, turns away, defended into the off side
shimmies down to defends a length delivery
nudges this one to short third for a single
nicely flighted outside off, gets front pad across as he defends
flicked past midwicket, uses his feet to get to the pitch of it, and gets a couple
pushes one down to long-on for a single
nicely swept away, right on top of it, rolls the wrists to keep it down, and along the ground and between the two deep leg-side fielders
bowled flatter this time, and defended
bunts this one off the pads, past short fine for a single
short, into the pads, played towards midwicket, gets a single

misses a stumping down the leg side? turns sharply off middle stump and beats Barath who has stepped out, Taibu fumbles but Barath was quick to go back and would have made for an interested replay had he indeed collected and whipped off the bails
pitches middle, turning in, played towards square leg
short turning into the pads, punched to midwicket
short delivery, cut away, can't beat point
fired into the pads, finds square leg as he helps it along
punched down the ground for a single
good work, dives full length to his right and deflects this push towards midwicket, saves a single
turning into the pads, whipped away, right of deep midwicket, gets a couple
dances down the track, ends up dragging this intended straight hit towards midwicket - along the ground
short delivery, pushed down the ground, and wide of long-on enough to come back for a second
pushed down straight to long-on this time, gets a single
flicked away off the pads, and gets a single to square leg
well bowled, goes straight with the arm and cramps him as he looks to punch it into the off side
looks to flick this into the on side, finds midwicket
shortish ball, gets an easy single to long-off
short delivery, cuts again, can't get it past point
fuller delivery this time, pushed down to long-on for a single
shortish delivery, can't get it past square leg
waits for it an extra second, flicks it past square leg and gets a single
Chanders rocks back and cuts it past point
steps out, lofts him down the ground, bounces in front of long-on
legbreak right away, pitches middle and leg and turns away, defended towards cover
full on the pads, swept away, straight to short fine
dances down the track, gets it square of fine leg, and comes back for two
full outside leg, goes for the sweep, but gets leg-byes
full ball, pushed down to long-on for a single
shortish, turning into in, and punched back to the bowler
short ball, pulled away, wide of midwicket, gets a couple

slog-swept, and Utseya gets his second wicket! it perhaps bounced a touch on him, and instead of going towards midwicket, it goes straight down the throat of long-on. The pressure exerted by the spinners have worked here
looks for a single to long-off, can't create distance between Utseya and the bowler
shorter delivery, cut to sweeper-cover
turning into the pads, played midwicket
another flick shot, can't get it past midwicket
into the pads, nudged around the corner for a single
full toss outside off, played back to the bowler
on the pads, played with soft hands towards midwicket
shorter, hits down the ground, can't get it past Cremer
looks for a tip-and-run, but has hit it a bit too powerfully to midwicket
still not off the mark, full ball on the pads, can't beat short fine leg
shortish, punched down the ground, gets a single
Chigumbura runs straight into the square-leg umpire as he looks to prevent a single, but they come through easily
nice sweep shot, a welcome boundary if ever there was one, over the in field, and square enough of fine leg
looks to run it past short third, but the ball doesn't have much pace on it
pushed down the ground, gets a single to long-on
presses forward and defends off the front foot
lovely lovely shot, just gets to the pitch of it, and plays a nice little pick-up over wide long-on, minimum effort for a six
full delivery, gets a single to long-on
short delivery, hurries onto him, he punches it straight to midwicket
gets a single down to long-off, innocuous delivery outside off
back of a length, and pushed down to long-on
pitches outside leg, looks for the sweep, the legbreak beats him, but the pads are covering the leg stump
starts off with a googly, interesting chap, and Cahnders defends outside off
another one that goes away, Chanders drives him down the ground, what a guy two googlies right up
and a third googly, and it beats him outside leg
googly again, big appeal for lbw as Ramdin just defends on the front foot, playing for the legbreak, pitches just outside off, turning, Taufel reckons it's going down
swept away, plays for the offbreak this time and gets a single
again turns away from the left-hand batsman, punches it to midwicket for one
Ramdin sweeps again, and gets a single
overpitched, gets an easy single to long-on
swept away powerfully, gets just a single to fine leg
flicked off the pads, gets a single wide of mid-on
short, and cut away easily to sweeper-cover for a single
nice shot, makes room early, and cuts from in front of the body, and finds the gap past point, gets a couple
looks to turn it off the pads, can't beat midwicket
overpitched, played down the ground for a single
quicker one, perhaps the flipper, stays back and plays it with an open face
another googly, pitched outside off, and Ramdin looks to cut this one - still not reading? - the bat comes down just in time
full delivery again, driven down to long-on for one
goes for the reverse-sweep to a low full toss - the seam-up delivery - connects, but can't beat short fine
another googly, gets a single to backward point
starts off with an lbw shout, but it is sliding down with the angle from round the stumps. Chanders just played down the wrong line
drops it at his feet, and Ramdin calls him through for a quick single
holds its line outside off, and Ramdin is beaten on the drive, help still for seamers, good pitch
short and wide, and cut away to deep point
length delivery, looks to turn it to third man, but is early into the shot
slower short ball, Chanders manages to keep it down as he pulls it
nicely chipped over extra cover, superb shot but lazy running, and they take two when the third was one
short, and cut away for a single to sweeper-cover
seam-up, into the pads, paddled to short fine leg, it bounces in front of Elton who gets his body behind it even though he doesn't field cleanly
short and wide again, cut away square of point, but not enough power as it holds up just before reaching the boundary
quicker, seam-up delivery, angled into the pads, gets the toe end towards cover
sweeps off the leg-stump line, finds short fine leg
short, and crisply pulled away, keeps it down too, but it will be just a single
slower delivery, Chanders is squared up as he plays it to cover
pushed wide of cover for a single
short delivery, slower than expected, hence cut in front of square, Cremer fumbles at cover and allows a single
short, no room, Chanders plays it back to the bowler
shortish again, plays with an open face, but finds backward point
Ramdin backs away for the cut shot, and is beaten by a fullish legbreak
drives down the ground this time and gets a single

Ramdin wants a single to short fine leg, but Chanders, the striker, doesn't respond, and Ramdin runs and dives back into the crease. Fair enough that it was Ramdin's call, but there wasn't a single there
fails to make contact on a sweep shot, beats everything, but called leg-byes by the umpire - it was way away from the body here
manufactures the cut shot again, makes room and plays it from in front of the stumps, gets a single to deep point
quicker one, pulled down the ground for a single
reverse-sweep right away, gets a top edge but clears short fine for a couple
short delivery, pulled away, gets a single to deep square leg
nicely bowled, pitches leg, turns towards off, no room, Chanders defends
pushed away past cover, finds the gap in the deep, and comes back for the second to complete an even-paced fifty
short, hit wide of long-on, gets a single
pushed down the ground for a single to long-on
looks to cut one that is too full, and is duly beaten
slightly short of a length, hurries onto him, he manages to only hit it back to Cremer
pitched up on the pads, gets a single to long-on
flat delivery, pushed down to long-on for one
makes room, goes inside-out, gets a single to long-off
sweeps, early into the shot, gets the back of the bat, over the keeper, gets a single before fine leg comes around
seam-up quicker delivery, played straight to midwicket
looks for the reverse sweep, can't beat cover
regulation sweep this time, much more effective, goes finer of deep square leg, and gets him four - good improvisation as he moved inside the line to make sure he hits it fine enough
goes for the big shot over the on side, gets the inside half of the bat for a single

soft dismissal, short delivery, Ramdin goes for the pull, but it comes into him and sort of rushes on too, cramps him up and he ends up pulling it straight down midwicket's throat. Not sure if he still played for the legbreak - Maruma is yet to bowl one, by the way, he has bowled all googlies and the occasional seam-up quicker ones

another soft wicket, poor running here, and Deonarine and Chanders - best friends from what it seems - involved in a run-out again! It is a quicker delivery, turned around the corner, and Deonarine sets off immediately, Chanders - though he never said no - ambles up the pitchcasually, and Sibanda hits the stumps direct. Chanders gives up way before Sibanda runs in, and to his right, to field this one
pitched outside leg, beats a poke from Deonarine
pitched off, defended back to the bowler
short, cut away straight to point
fuller, but driven straight to cover
shortish delivery, pushed down to long-on for single
flicked from outside off, but with the turn, to get a single
looks to flick this off the pads, but this doesn't turn and beats him
again the straight delivery beats him as he looks to push it into the leg side
gets this push wide of a diving Price for a single
flat delivery around off, guides it to short third for a single
flicked away uppishly, and finds the gap in the deep on the leg side, comes back for two
another flick shot, this time gets a single only because he can't beat midwicket
drives down to long-on for a single
goes for the big shot over the off side, but ends up going into the on side because the ball doesn;t come on, and he gets too far under it, Cremer runs in from deep midwicket, but drops it
pushed down to long-on for a single
yorker, dot ball, well bowled
lovely square-drive, not much room, but he creates space by opening the face and beats point, and gets four
makes room and cuts this time, Cremer fumbles at cover and allows a single
leading edge on that intended extravagant Bravo flick as it stops on it, but the edge lands short of long-on
short, gets under it, pulls, but will get just a single to deep square leg
jumps out of the track, looks to go over the on side, misses, but gets a leg-bye
down the pitch again, yorks himself, gets a single past a diving Price, who admonishes himself
nice shot, makes room, and punches a shortish delivery through the cover gap

full delivery, driven inside-out, through extra cover, doesn't race along the outfield, Chigumbura runs from long-on and makes a diving save. Has to make two attempts to save a single as the ball hits his body and almost goes for four
driven down to long-off for a single
leg-stump line, misses out on the sweep shot and gets a leg-bye
goes for the big shot over long-on, gets the inside half of the bat, and it falls just over midwicket
makes room as he charges down the wicket, and goes inside-out over mid-off, finally a boundary for the desperate-looking batsmen
short delivery, cuts it, can't get it past cover-point
sweeps to square leg, will get just a single
jumps out nof the crease, is beaten in the flight, and ends up defending it
superb running by Bravo, hit just metres wide of long-off, but Bravo runs fast, initiates the second and makes it to the danger end. Price is not happy, wants a change of the long-off fielder
misses out on a sweep shot, and gets one leg-bye
goes for big heave over the leg side, gets the inside half for a single
that;s a timely biggie for West Indies, it is fired into the pads and Deonarine backs away, gets under it, and lofts it over the man at square leg
low full toss, hit one bounce to long-on
goes for loft over extra cover, the offbreak means he ends up slicing it straight to cover-point
wide down the leg side, and they will run a single too as it deflects off Taibu to short fine leg
steps out and goes for the big flick again, and is beaten by the spin and is hit in the thigh pad
goes against the spin, can't find the gap in the off side, gets only a single
comes forward and nudges it to short third man for a single
against the spin again and straight to the ring fielder again
spinning into him and turned around the corner for one
goes for the yorker, misses his direction, and gives away a wide down the leg side
tries an inswinging yorker, turns into a low full toss, flicked away for two, square of fine leg
gets the yorker right this time, single to midwicket
slower bouncer, nicely bowled, Bravo delays the upper cut, but is still early into the shot, signalled one bouncer for the over
follows it up with a superb yorker, following him too as he backs away to make room
makes room this time to go inside-out, places it wide of long-off to get a couple

that flick just hasn't come right for Bravo today, and even as this is angled into his pads he is early into the shot, and the leading edge lobs to mid-off, and Matsikenyeri runs from extra cover to complete the catch
turned away with the turn, gets a single to midwicket
dropped, mind you it was firmly hit back at the bowler, the ball brushes his hand and goers straight into Taufel, at least two runs saved by Taufel
full delivery, hit wide of long-on, and they run well to make it back for two
another full delivery and they run fast again, and come back for two to wide long-on
biffs this one, doesn't connect, gets a single to midwicket
dropped at long-on by Maruma, low full toss, hit down the ground, Maruma comes too far in and ends up palming it overhead into the boundary
goes for the big sweep shot, will get just a single to deep backward square
is beaten on the sweep shot, gets one leg-bye
that's the power of Pollard! Steps out, it seems he has got too close to the pitch of the ball, but gets enough power in it to clear long-on and hit the roof of the stands

the Revenge of the Leggie! Sees Pollard charge at him, bowls this one wide, the break takes it away, and beats him, and it's a comfortable stumping for Taibu, and again Zimbabwe strike before West Indies can inflict too much damage
nice sweep shot, powerfully hit over midwicket, clean strike, and finds the gap between deep midwicket and long-on
big sweep shot! this will hurt Zimbabwe! C lean connection, with the spin, and the shoulders of a fast bowler, way over square leg
into the pads, flicked away to fine leg
full toss and wide outside off, called wide
low fulltoss, goes inside-out, wide of extra cover, gets a couple
second wide in the last over, gets the length right - a yorker - but too far wide of off

eventful delivery! Rampaul goes for the pull shot, Utseya runs back from square leg but the top edge clears him and suddenly he sees midwicket running in and jams his head into Maruma's shin while trying to avoid the collision, and has hit himself hard. Meanwhile, Rampaul tries to sneak a third, but Chigumbura collects the throw with one hand and makes sure he doesn't disturb the bail before he collects it, and then runs him out
gets the yorker right, will be just a single to long-on
Miller to face, and Miller misses a full and straight delivery and is bowled
comes down the track and hits one bounce to long-on, and Sammy is quick enough to come back for two

inn2.comm: looks to cut, the ball nips back in, rolls off towards mid-on
left alone outside off, doesn't carry through to Ramdin

what a yorker! 90mph, just short of the crease, and through him even before the bat comes down, and the off stump cartwheels. The last time Roach bowled such a yorker to Vusi, his bat came down, but the ball broke through the bat and took the stump. No bat here, what a ripper to begin here
back of a length, 91mph, defended
guides this one down to third man for a single
back of a length, rising delivery, beats Masakadza as he fends at it outside off
slightly holds its line outside off, steers it to third man for a single
back of a length, rising delivery, tucks Hamilton up, hits the bat hard
helped away behind square on the on side for a single
almost chopped on, looks to run this down to third man, but the ball comes in and takes the inside half of the bat and bounces wide of the off stump
angling into the batsman, played towards midwicket
again, back of a length, on target, hitting the bat hard, played back to him
length ball, around off, 91mph, played towards cover
fast short-of-a-length delivery, into his ribs before he properly gets the bat around, fended off, manages to keep it down
played wide of backward point to get off strike
90mph, full and on off, defended to the bowler
goes for the expansive drive outside off, ends up playing inside the line, is beaten
just back of a length, but it bounces chest high, Taylor fends it and keeps it down
pulled away handsomely, he is on front foot, but transfers the weight back and pulls it square of square leg
looks for that little single to third man and is beaten

missed run-out, Taylor wants a single to backward point, Pollard is quick and Taylor is rightly sent back, Pollard misses the direct hit, but there was enough time there for him to throw it to the fielder, Miller, who was in quickly
back of a length, defended to cover
gets on top of the bounce, and he punches it to cover

another front-foot pull shot, and with a man back there who was placed there after the boundary first ball of this over. Again he is no the front foot, sees the ball short, just transfers the weight back and pulls, square of deep square leg
short of a length, too quick again, hits the bat even before it comes down properly, the inside edge goes into his pad
upper-cut, superb shot, gets under it and goes over point as opposed to third man, and unlike in Guyana - where the shot got him out - he hit it hard this time
lunges forward and leaves it alone, Ponting-style
tucked into the pads, turned around the corner for a single
back of a length, around off, defended towards point
outside off, left alone and Roach has over-stepped
gets the yorker in, will be a single to third man
gives him the charge, Ravi bowls short and follows him, manages to get a single to short fine leg
back of a length outside off, gets him on the handle and the glove as he defends
into the hips, worked away for a single
charges down again, Rampaul tries the short one into the body, ends up bowling a wide down the leg side
worked away off the hips for a single
around off, short of a length, and defended
into the hips, and nurdled away for a single
digs it in short, Taylor defends it back to the bowler
driven on the up, finds the gap too through the cover, and times it well enough to take it far enough for a three
nice on-drive, goes for the yorker, it's a half-volley, and he pushes it straight of mid-on, another three
defends this outside off, towards cover
nicely played, just short of being a yorker, opens the face on it and places it between cover point and backward point
pulls the length back this time, defended to cover
opens the face, wide of backward point, gets a single
looks to work it fine, misses, but gets a leg-bye
he takes the deep square leg on and pulls magnificently, over the deep fielder, just a flick of wrists and the power from strong arms
punched wide of point for one
length ball outside off, defended to cover
presses forward and defends another delivery to cover
whatay shot! over-pitched all right, but driven straight down the ground, welcome back Bravo, to Masakadza's high elbow
shorter in length this time, hit to mid-on
steered to third man for one
left alone outside off
looks to drive on the up, wide of off, gets the inside part of the bat, back to the bowler
cut away off the front foot, gets a single
holds its line outside off, and beats a poke, seam movement for Sammy right away
this one comes in with the angle, defended back to the bowler
pull shot off the front foot, the top edge flies over the keeper, not short enough for the originally intended shot, perfect length for the one that resulted
back of a length, rises a bit, defended to the bowler
pushed back to the bowler, just back of a length again
gone, caught and bowled, Taylor drives at a length delivery, bat turns in the hand and offers an easy return catch
into the hips, gets some extra bounce, but Masakadza gets a single to fine leg
wide of off, left alone
driven on the up, Bravo does well to stop it on the follow through
drops at his feet and comes through for one, all thanks to Masakdza's early call
looks to pull again, early into the shot, gets a single off the glove
short of a length, around off, pushed back to the bowler
almost another return catch, this one stopped at Hamilton, it falls wide enough on the on side of the pitch
Taibu wants a single straight to midwicket and is rightly sent back, but Deonarine misses the direct hit, which would have found the dive short
comes forward and defends a length delivery
gives him the charge and pulls, Sammy sees him coming down and digs it in, Hamilton goes through with the pull and gets enough back to clear the in field - by the way, the Bowling Powerplay is on
helped away off the pads for a single

and Sammy strikes last ball of the over again! brushes the outside edge, holds its line ever so slightly, pitched just back of a length, around off-stump line, making him play, and taking a thin edge through
superb slower ball, beats him all ends up, the leg-before appeal is stifled because it is headed down leg
steered away for one
and he is gone first ball! Bravo gets one to bend in and right up to the stumps, Stuart gets a long way across, is beaten by the swing, and is caught right in front
another inswinger, Lamb uses his bat to defend one in front of middle stump
driven square, one bounce to Pollard at backward point, and the crowd in excited. The crowd has sort of built up now
one bounce to Pollard again, who throws it up as if it was a catch, but the crowd doesn't buy it
pushes a length delivery back to the bowler

three in three overs for Sammy! and this is the big one, Masakadza! looks for that little single down to third man, the ball holds its line slightly, and it's enough to get the edge, West Indies - and the crowd - are elated
gets off the mark, working the ball off the hips square of fine leg for a couple
back of a length outside off, defended
worked off the pads again, gets a single this time
this one jumps at Lamb, who takes the bottom hand as he fends at it, and it goes wide of slip for a single
square-driven, and Pollard makes a diving save to his right at backward point
tries the bouncer, Lamb sways out of the line
down the leg side, misses the big shot, gets a wide
plays this with an open face, towards point
full, on the pads, flicked away for a single
a yorker meanwhile, dug out by Elton
gets an inside edge as he looks to drive, he is safe, though
chops this one down to third man for a single
full delivery on middle and leg, defended
pulled away, sits up to be hit, and he collects four impressive runs
into the pads, worked wide of mid-on for a single
length ball, around off, defended to cover
just short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
runs this down to square of third man, comes back for a second
slight movement away, beaten outside off, well bowled
after one holds its line, Roach gets one to come in, and it beats Chigumbura and catches him in front of stumps, at the crease, and hits him just inside the line. Roach kisses the badge on the shirt
nice bouncer, cramps him up with one that follows him, just about manages to duck under it
bouncer followed by the full and straight delivery, Maruma defends it on the front foot
back of a length, stays back and defends it
length ball around off, driven nicely, but straight to mid-off
slightly shorter, defended off the front foot
looks to drive, gets the inside half of the bat, takes a single
offcutter, Maruma equal to it, getting the bat down in time to defend
short of a length, pushed to cover
worked away off the pads, comes back for two as it is hit square of fine leg
dug in short, sways out of the line easily
loose shot outside off, beaten by the pace as he looks to drive
back of a length, around off, defended
defended with an open face
yorker, just outside off, beats the bat, what if it had been straighter?
beats him with pace with one angling down the leg side
on target, just outside off, defended off the back foot
again gets to hold its line outside, gets him to commit to the shot and beats him
another one holds its line, another one bites the dust! seems it would angle in to the batsman, and then straightens enough to beat him and kiss the top of off stump, West Indies all over it
full delivery on the stumps, pushed down to long-on
left alone outside off
nicely driven on the up, through the covers, takes a single to sweeper-cover
Roach goes for the bouncer again, but this is too high and called a wide
wide, and nicely cut away, square enough of third man to come back for two
lovely catch CG! goes for the big drive, gets a healthy edge, Gayle at first slip dives to his left and takes it one-handed, what a blinder that is!
yorker outside off, but oversteps
backs away, goes for the big cut over covers, misses as it bounces high
short delivery, fended outside off, keeps it down
yorker goes through him, but it is outside off
full delivery outside off, defended to point
looks to work it off the pads, misses, the ball hits him in the thigh
length delivery around middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
looks to run it down to third man, can't beat point
gets this full delivery wide of mid-on and comes through for a single
length ball, holds its line again, defended off the outside half of the bat
goes past the outside edge, he has bowled this delivery really well, just holds its line, and beats a defensive shot outside off
looks for the cut shot, and is beaten outside off
nice accurate bouncer, can't get out of the way, gets him on the glove, luckily for him it doesn't pop up
full and wide, gets a thick edge for a single
punches a shortish delivery to sweeper-cover
pushes a back-of-a-length delivery to cover
upper-cuts, square of third man, Cremer slips while turning back for the second and stays in his crease
beats the batsman again, with the angle, lbw shout, but it could be going down and could be high too, so too much going against the shout
tucks him up with one into the hips
fuller, in-coming delivery, presses forward, defends
looks to cut, g=makes good connection, can't get it past point
fuller delivery, outside off, hit back to Sammy
played with an open face to point
nice bouncer, took some effort in ducking under it, he had to do that fast as it was a sharp delivery
back of a length, gets behind this one and defends
yorker outside off, dug out nicely
drives at a full delivery outside off, is beaten
full delivery on the pads, nicely worked away for a couple
slower ball, into the pads, misses it as he looks to work it down to fine leg
throws his bat at one outside off, gets the inside half towards wide of mid-on, gets a single
full, outside off, hit to cover on the bounce
defends a length ball towards mid-on
full outside off, Utseya comes forward and shoulders arms
steered away nicely to third man for a single
back of a length, tucks him up, played back to the bowler
and straight away an uppish shot, sharp inswing, but the ball chips over midwicket for a couple
inswing again, beats him, but it is clearly going down the leg side
uppishly played towards midwicket again, one bounce this time, Sammy goes for the non-striker's end stumps, and gives away four overthrows
forward-defensive, nice correct shot
full, driven on the up, can't beat mid-on
slower ball, played to the on side
almost a five-for! dropped by Gayle diving to his right at first slip, definitely a much easier catch than the one Gayle took earlier. Sammy holds his head, doesn't look towards skipepr, though
comes forward and defends
driven nicely outside off, can't get it past cover
looks to run it to third man, can't get it past Pollard at point

Sammy holds his head, is on his knees as he sees an uppish shot that lands way in front of mid-on. He may have not picked up a five-for, but Sammy has bowled really well today in this unbroken 10-over spell
and he has upper-cut this one straight to third man! short and wide and he goes for it, Miller comes in a couple of paces and completes the catch
and he seems the perfect No. 11, plays outside the line of a straight delivery that somehow misses the off stump
nice shot, on the pads, flicked away like a batsman, gets two
back of a length, defended one bounce to the bowler
fuller ball, beats him, angling down the leg side, hence only half an appeal
comes forward and defends a length delivery
starts with one down the leg side, worked away
spin for Miller there, beats Price outside off - that's what he does for living
gets bat to ball this time, defended to cover
hit down the ground, powerfully, but but straight to mid-on
played with an open face to point
beaten outside off again, goes wide of the crease, slows it up, and then gets it to spin away
guides this short delivery over slips, brings up the 100 for Zimbabwe
hit straight back to Bravo, on the bounce
slower short delivery, Utseya looks to cut, misses
fuller slower one this time, played along the ground towards midwicket
long way down the leg side
defended off the front foot, towards mid-on
full delivery, hit to mid-on
quick delivery on target, played with a straight bat
short, looks to give it everything, hits it straight into the ground
dropped by Rampaul, running backwards from mid-on, does everything right, gets under it, but can't hold on, perhaps not balanced under it
defended with an open face, towards point
all over for Zimbabwe, cut powerfully, but straight to Gayle at short point, head high and held easily. Lowest score at Arnos Vale!
